1
00:00:01,320 --> 00:00:03,120
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

2
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:14,160
KAHLER-JEX: Traditionally, revolutions
begin with a gunshot or a call to arms.

3
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:16,480
But when future historians look back

4
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:18,800
to find the seed
of the golden age of the Kahler,

5
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:23,160
they'll see it began here,
began now, with an idea.

6
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:26,720
The intention is to create
a living weapon,

7
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:31,680
a multi-faceted war machine
that doesn't tire, doesn't malfunction.

8
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,560
The subjects were chosen

9
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:35,400
from our last remaining
military academy,

10
00:00:35,480 --> 00:00:37,520
as they had to be healthy

11
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:39,680
and resilient enough
to survive the procedures.

12
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:43,880
A degree of duplicity was
necessary to secure their participation.

13
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:47,120
They were told they'd been
selected for peace-keeping missions

14
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:49,040
on off-world colonies.

15
00:00:59,840 --> 00:01:05,000
All weaponry, radar and intel
will be literally fused with the host

16
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:08,640
so that soldier and artillery
are one.

17
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:19,520
(BEEPING)

18
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:28,520
Subject 6. Kahler-Tech.

19
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:32,000
The idea made flesh.

20
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:34,640
(POWERING UP)

